text: Confessing your feeling to your crush is NOT worth it boys  keep this in mind  You only live once   shoot your shot   you ll never know unless you do it  These are just   of many misleading and unhelpful quotes intended to encourage people to tell their crush how they feel I must say from experience  I ve had   crushes who I ve confessed to  I told them how I felt and I got rejected  firstly  I know why I got rejected because these two situations I was really young and stupid and could have done so much better so me getting rejected wasn t a surprise  Sure  I m just one guy out of millions  but trust me when I say  getting rejected hurts  a lot   Unless you and your crush have both given really obvious signs that you both reciprocate the same feelings towards each other  confessing just isn t worth it  you re better of just keeping your mind off the girl Go watch a movie  start exercising  and try your best not to think of them  if you feel like they ll say no or you just want to get it over with  don t  just leave it  The fact of the matter is that if they like you back they would probably tell you  without you telling them first  I myself currently have a crush who I spend days thinking about and asking myself how she s so fucking pretty without makeup and how she has the best personality  well it s dawned on me that she does not reciprocate the same feelings that I have  and I was really close to just confessing and saying  the worst she can say is no  but I realised that if it s guaranteed that she would say no  then there s no point in going through the pain in confessing Confessing your feelings to a girl has like a   success rate and unless you see that she likes you back  those odds aren t going to be in your favour This applies mainly to boys who have female crushes
summary: Confessing your feelings to your crush is not worth it. Confessing to a girl has a low success rate. If a girl likes you back, she would tell you without you telling her first.    He has a crush on a girl who doesn't reciprocate his feelings.
